Title: Stranger in the Family

reviewText: Dissociative Disorder is a decision deep down within the psyche of the person, that no one really understands.  Whether this is a substantiated case or a feigned condition is my first thought???  If a person hates themselves and who they are enough is it possible they would establish a new identity to be someone new???  This movie raises a lot of questions in my mind.  Terri Garr perhaps over plays her role, but I don't feel like it was an authentic portrayal of the case.  I can't explain why exactly, but it just doesn't convince me.
Title: Stranger in the Family
